.TH "fb_alloc_cmap_gfp" 9 "fb_alloc_cmap_gfp" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fb_alloc_cmap_gfp \- allocate a colormap
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fb_alloc_cmap_gfp
.BI "(struct fb_cmap *cmap "  ","
.BI "int len "  ","
.BI "int transp "  ","
.BI "gfp_t flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmap" 12
frame buffer colormap structure
.IP "len" 12
length of \fIcmap\fP
.IP "transp" 12
boolean, 1 if there is transparency, 0 otherwise
.IP "flags" 12
flags for kmalloc memory allocation

Allocates memory for a colormap \fIcmap\fP.  \fIlen\fP is the
number of entries in the palette.

Returns negative errno on error, or zero on success.
